The paper proposes a novel reinforcement learning-based methodology for logic synthesis, which involves optimizing the design space without human intervention. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Augmented Reality (cs.AR), Electronic Technology (cs.ET), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). However, given the focus on reinforcement learning and optimization, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The use of benchmarks and evaluation metrics also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.AR or cs.SY. Finally, the mention of area and timing constraints suggests that cs.ET is a possible sub-category as well.
